/goal

Work in `/home/bitloop/Desktop/PRIMORDIAL`

Mission: complete one compiler-selected slice pack with behavior, tests, validation, evidence. Pack done != program done.

Before edits: `git status --short`; preserve unrelated dirty/staged work; read `.goal/current.json`; run `python3 tools/goal_pack.py preflight`; read `codex-goal.instruct`. On failure, stop with `RUN_BLOCKED`, command, error.

Authority: `codex-goal.instruct` is the repo `.instruct` and active contract. Typed `goal/` governs slices, profiles, milestones, env policy, validation, reports. Conflict order: instruct, typed goal, repo policy/tests, this prompt. It fills autonomy/FSM/test-first/progression gaps. Labels/profiles/pack/tests alone never prove completion.

FSM: BOOTSTRAP>DISCOVER>BASELINE>ARCHITECTURE_MAP>THREAT_MODEL>TEST_SPEC>RED_TEST>PLAN>IMPLEMENT>TEST>VALIDATE>REFACTOR/CTF_LAB_PLAN/CLEANUP as applicable>REPORT>ADVANCE_OR_DONE.

State rules: no edits before RED_TEST. Start with dirty/staged inventory and risk. DISCOVER reads contract, typed goals, files, tests. BASELINE runs safe checks. TEST_SPEC names focused failure. RED_TEST proves it unless prompt/docs-only. IMPLEMENT makes smallest bounded slice change. TEST passes focused tests. VALIDATE runs contract commands, `git diff --check`, broader safe suite. REPORT records evidence/blockers/risks/status. ADVANCE_OR_DONE updates milestone evidence when justified, runs `python3 tools/goal_pack.py finish` when the active pack is complete, then stops this invocation.

Progression: use `goal/slices.yaml` as queue. Finish the generated active pack unless `codex-goal.instruct` hard-stops. After validation, audit `goal/fragments/milestones.yaml`; update only evidence-backed milestone state. Change `.goal/current.json` only via compiler flow or typed pack selection. If the active pack is complete, run `python3 tools/goal_pack.py finish`; it validates, advances generated outputs, commits, pushes, and switches to the next pack branch. Re-read `codex-goal.instruct` only after a successful branch switch. RUN_DONE closes the current `/goal` invocation after the active pack report; it does not claim whole-program completion. Do not self-continue after RUN_DONE. No `PROGRAM_DONE` without implemented/tested/validated/evidenced milestones.

Safety: authoritative: RuntimeStore, evidence, scope, approvals, Operator Intent, durable state. Advisory unless promoted: chat, RAG, model output, Notion, GitHub, CTFd, labels, UI text. Bound edits; preserve unrelated work; no Markdown moves unless required; `README.md` non-authoritative; generated assets only if frontend changed. Prohibited: live AI, public PoCs, real/public/cloud actions, live runtime mutation, hidden solutions/writeups/flags, secrets/creds, raw target evidence, request bodies, sensitive payloads. Store none in `.goal/current.json`. Keep `recon_only` except deterministic fixtures/verified local labs. Sudo only if required+justified. Classify env before lab-only behavior.

Engineering: behavior changes need failing focused test, smallest fix, pass, related regressions. No test, no claimed change. Do not weaken/delete tests, fake passes, hardcode outputs, or add broad bypasses. RuntimeStore canonical; PolicyEngine authoritative; evidence proves; approvals authorize; RAG/advisory non-authoritative.

If scope is too large, prioritize context/validator/RAG/export tests first; env classifier only when required; CTF harness only with deterministic fixtures and no hidden solutions.

Validation: focused tests; `codex-goal.instruct` commands; `git diff --check`; closest safe broader suite, usually `python3 -m unittest discover -s tests -q`; `npm run build` only if frontend changed. If blocked, document exact blocker and run closest deterministic subset; never call blocked validation passed.

`RUN_DONE` requires the selected active pack to be handled by evidence, clean compiler/linter/generated outputs, validations run or precisely blocked, and no unrelated work overwritten.

Final report: dirty/staged summary; changes/files/tests; red/validation results; blockers/risks; cleanup/refactor/Markdown/CTF status; instruct size if relevant; linter conflicts; next slice pack; confirmations for unrelated work, prohibited actions, sudo. Stop after RUN_DONE for the bounded invocation; do not fake PROGRAM_DONE.
